Neville Kennard https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neville_Kennard 0 Neville Kennard (1900 – 30 December 1963) was a twentieth century variety entertainer from England, most active in the 1920s, 1930s and 1940s. He was a prolific writer of sketches and was one of the most famous names associated with the concert party form of entertainment.
